getName

public String getName()
The name of the hosted service. This name is the DNS prefix name and can be used to access the hosted service. For example, if the service name is MyService you could access the access the service by calling: http://MyService.cloudapp.net

getCategory

public com.google.common.base.Optional<String> getCategory()
The repository classification of image. All user images have the category "User", but categories for other images could be, for example "Canonical"

getLocation

public com.google.common.base.Optional<String> getLocation()
The geo-location in which this media is located. The Location value is derived from storage account that contains the blob in which the media is located. If the storage account belongs to an affinity group the value is absent.

getAffinityGroup

public com.google.common.base.Optional<String> getAffinityGroup()
The affinity in which the media is located. The AffinityGroup value is derived from storage account that contains the blob in which the media is located. If the storage account does not belong to an affinity group the value is absent.

getMediaLink

public com.google.common.base.Optional<URI> getMediaLink()
The location of the blob in the blob store in which the media for the image is located. The blob location belongs to a storage account in the subscription specified by the value in the operation call. Example: http://example.blob.core.windows.net/disks/myimage.vhd

getEula
